12/05/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The ruling coalition parties -- Social Democratic Alliance for Macedonia, Democratic Union for Integration and the Liberal Democratic Party -- agreed Tuesday (11 May) that Hari Kostov would succeed President-elect Branko Crvenkovski in the post of prime minister.
They also agreed that that there would be personnel changes in the new government, but no change in the distribution of ministries among the three parties.
Crvenkovski takes the presidential oath before parliament Wednesday.
In other news Monday, Macedonia and Albania signed a two-year agreement on co-operation in the field of education and science.
Each country would acknowledge the other's university education diplomas and encourage joint scientific research.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 12/05/04;
A1 TV, ATA, MIA - 11/05/04)
